      "name": "1 medium tomato",
      "amount": "1 piece",
      "notes": "diced"
    },
    {
      "name": "2 cloves garlic",
      "amount": "4 pieces",
      "notes": "minced"
    },
    {
      "name": "1 onion",
      "amount": "1/4 of a medium-sized",
      "notes": "chopped finely"
    },
    {
      "name": "20 grams butter",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "unsalted"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt and pepper to taste",
      "amount": "",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "Blanch the diced tomato in boiling water for about 2 minutes. Remove from heat, place in cold water, and let cool.",
    "Once cooled, drain tomatoes, cut into halves if large, and remove seeds and skin.",
    "Heat butter in a pan over medium heat. Add garlic and onion, sauté until softened but not browned.",
    "Add the blanched tomato pieces to the pan. Stir-fry for about 5 minutes, seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.",
    "Serve hot or at room temperature as desired."
  ],
